{"title_page": "Bad (David Guetta and Showtek song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Bad\n| cover      = David Guetta Showtek Bad.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[David Guetta]] and [[Showtek]]<br/>featuring [[Vassy (singer)|Vassy]]\n| album      = [[Listen (David Guetta album)|Listen (Deluxe edition)]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2014|03|17|df=yes}}\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Big room house]]\n| length     = 2:50 <small>(radio edit)</small><br />4:30 <small>(extended mix)</small>\n| label      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Parlophone]]\n* [[Jack Back Records|Jack Back]]\n* What A Music\n}}\n| writer     = {{flatlist|\n* David Guetta\n* [[Showtek|Wouter Janssen]]\n* [[Showtek|Sjoerd Janssen]]\n* [[Giorgio Tuinfort]]\n* [[Sultan & Ned Shepard|Ossama Al Sarraf]]\n* [[Sultan & Ned Shepard|Ned Shepard]]\n* [[DJ Manian|Manuel Reuter]]\n* [[Vassy (singer)|Vassy]]\n* Nick Turpin\n}}\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* David Guetta\n* [[Showtek]]\n* [[Sultan & Ned Shepard]]\n* Manuel Reuter\n}}\n| chronology = [[David Guetta]]\n| prev_title = [[Shot Me Down]]\n| prev_year  = 2014\n| next_title = [[Blast Off (David Guetta and Kaz James song)|Blast Off]]\n| next_year  = 2014\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Showtek]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title = [[We Like to Party (Showtek song)|We Like to Party]]\n | prev_year  = 2013\n | title      = Bad\n | year       = 2014\n | next_title = Bouncer\n | next_year  = 2014\n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Vassy (singer)|Vassy]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title = Mad\n | prev_year  = 2014\n | title      = Bad\n | year       = 2014\n | next_title = Hustlin\n | next_year  = 2014\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Bad'''\" (also stylised as '''''BAD!''''') is a song by French music producer and DJ [[David Guetta]] and Dutch production duo [[Showtek]], featuring vocals from Australian singer [[Vassy (singer)|Vassy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-singles/?ye=2014&we=16|title=Le Top de la semaine : Top Singles ~ Semaine du 07 Avril 2014|publisher=Syndicat National de l'\u00e9dition Phonographique|date=April 2014|accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-04-26/france-songs|title=Billboard: France Songs ~ April 26, 2014|magazine=Billboard|date=April 2014|accessdate=17 April 2014}}</ref> It was released on 17 March 2014 as a single of the deluxe version from Guetta's studio album, ''[[Listen (David Guetta album)|Listen]]''. It was written and produced by Guetta, Showtek, [[Sultan & Ned Shepard]], and [[DJ Manian|Manuel Reuter]] and it was co-written by [[Giorgio Tuinfort]], [[Sultan & Ned Shepard|Ossama Al Sarraf]], [[Vassy (singer)|Vassy]], and Nick Turpin.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bad - Vassy|url=http://www.dr.dk/musik/titel/bad/9010261-1-1|publisher=[[DR (broadcaster)|DR]]|accessdate=16 May 2014|language=Danish}}</ref> The song entered and peaked on the [[UK Singles Chart]] at number 22. This track has since topped the chart in Finland and Norway. The song, which features vocals from Vassy, features her with an [[Auto-Tune]]d voice; reviews were critical of the effects applied to the vocals.\n\n==Music video==\nThe video which is a lyrics video is on both David Guetta's YouTube and [[VEVO]] account. It is a total of 2 minutes and 50 seconds long. It was released on April 10, 2014.\n\nIt starts out with a girl fighting zombies while the zombies dance as a reference to [[Thriller (song)|Michael Jackson's \"Thriller\"]]. Suddenly, she falls in love with one of the zombies who goes up to her, and the two run away from the military, who are chasing them.\n\n==Critical reception==\nMike Wass of [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] wrote: \"The grittier electro-house sound of 'Bad' is perhaps an indication that the hitmaker is moving away from the commercial dance sound of his last LP. Former hardstyle duo Showtek ensure that the beats come thicker and faster than ever, while Australian dance diva Vassy provides the instantly catchy hook \u2014 albeit in a heavily autotuned voice.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wass|first1=Mike|title=David Guetta Teams Up With Showtek And Vassy For New Floorfiller \"Bad\": Listen|url=http://www.idolator.com/7510226/david-guetta-showtek-vassy-bad|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|accessdate=3 August 2014|date=17 March 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download\n| title1  = Bad\n| note1   = featuring Vassy) (extended mix\n| length1 = 4:30\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed = yes\n| headline = Digital download - radio edit\n| title1   = Bad\n| note1    = featuring Vassy) (radio edit\n| length1  = 2:50\n}}\n\n==Charts and certifications==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2014)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|5|artist=David Guetta & Showtek feat. Vassy|song=Bad|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia Dance ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>[http://www.ariacharts.com.au/chart/dance-singles ARIA Australian Top 20 Dance Singles] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511020224/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/chart/dance-singles |date=2013-05-11 }}. ARIA. 24 April 2014. Retrieved 24 February 2014.</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|15|artist=David Guetta & Showtek feat. Vassy|song=Bad|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|12|artist=David Guetta & Showtek feat. Vassy|song=Bad|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|16|artist=David Guetta & Showtek feat. Vassy|song=Bad|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canada|20|artist=David Guetta|song=Bad|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|Colombia ([[National-Report]])<ref name=\"ColombiaNR\">{{cite web|title=Top 10 M\u00fasica Nacional Radio |language=Spanish |url=http://co